{"id": 232044536, "title": "Watch: Shivraj Chouhan takes oath as Cabinet minister amid loud cheers - India Today", "text": "Senior BJP leader and former Madhya Pradesh chief minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan took the oath as a Union Cabinet Minister on Sunday. He was one of the first five ministers sworn in after Prime Minister Narendra Modi's oath. Chauhan served as the chief minister of Madhya Pradesh from 2005 to 2018 and again from 2020 to 2023, making him the longest-serving Chief Minister of the state. Chauhan contested the Lok Sabha election from Vidisha constituency and defeated Congress\u2019s Pratabhanu Sharma by over eight lakh votes.", "summary": "<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/india/video/watch-shivraj-chouhan-takes-oath-as-cabinet-minister-amid-loud-cheers-2551060-2024-06-09\"> <img align=\"left\" hspace=\"2\" height=\"180\" width=\"305\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/video/202406/shivraj-chouhan-oath-093341563-16x9_0.jpg?VersionId=TmDB0q_83lNLSnQQ20B8aAzYUP2KnEEV\"> </a> Watch: Shivraj Chouhan takes oath as Cabinet minister amid loud cheers", "url": "https://www.indiatoday.in/india/video/watch-shivraj-chouhan-takes-oath-as-cabinet-minister-amid-loud-cheers-2551060-2024-06-09", "image": "https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/video/202406/shivraj-chouhan-oath-093341563-16x9_0.jpg?VersionId=TmDB0q_83lNLSnQQ20B8aAzYUP2KnEEV?size=647:363", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 15:34:45", "author": "India Today Video Desk", "authors": ["India Today Video Desk"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.531}